{"type":"message","id":"61c892cd","parentId":"d1373219","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:05:00.528Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The scripting define symbols include `GASDK` (on platforms 1 - Standalone, and 4 - Android, etc.). This is why the `using GiantSDK.Parent;` directive is compiled in but the GiantSDK plugin/DLL is missing.\n\nLooking at line 634:\n```\n1: UNITY_POST_PROCESSING_STACK_V2;AMPLIFY_SHADER_EDITOR;TextMeshPro;GASDK;GuanFang;CRASH_SIGHT;PerfSight\n```\n\nPlatform 1 = Standalone (Windows/Mac/Linux). So when running in the editor on Windows, the `GASDK` define is present, causing the code to try to use `GiantSDK.Parent` which doesn't exist in this checkout.\n\nThis is a missing GiantSDK plugin issue. This isn't something I can fix - the GiantSDK plugin DLL needs to be present for these defines to work, or alternatively, the `GASDK` define needs to be removed from Standalone builds.\n\nHowever, since the GASDK define is there by design (probably for the actual game builds), the issue is that the GiantSDK plugin DLLs aren't included in the repository/checkout. This is likely intentional.\n\nBut wait - this is the test server update. The workflow says:\n1. First check git pull\n2. Then run Unity pipeline\n\nLet me check if the git pull was done recently, or if there were changes. Actually, looking at the subagent context more carefully - I was spawned specifically to \"执行 Unity 热更流水线\" and the main agent likely already did the git pull. Let me check if we simply need to fix the missing GiantSDK issue.\n\nActually, looking at the ERRORLEVEL from the bat file run:\n- The bat runs Unity which exits with the compiler errors\n- Unity in batch mode aborts when scripts have compiler errors\n\nThis is a blocking issue. Let me think about what I can do:\n\n1. I can't add the GiantSDK DLLs because I don't know where they are\n2. But I can check if there's some way to define the symbols differently for the pipeline\n\nWait, the pipeline is `BuildPipeline.RunHotUpdatePipeline`. This is a custom build pipeline, not a standard Unity build. Let me think about what the user normally does...\n\nActually, looking at the error more carefully - we're running on platform that has `GASDK` defined (Standalone Windows), which enables the `using GiantSDK.Parent;` and all the GiantSDK code. The GiantSDK plugin isn't in the Assets folder, which means either:\n1. It was gitignored and needs to be restored\n2. Or it needs to be added\n\nLet me check if there's a GiantSDK somewhere in the project.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_rAWwKFQXoQL6mSKNmxVG2249","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\" -Filter \"*GiantSDK*\" -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue -Depth 5 | Select-Object FullName, Length | Format-Table -AutoSize","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":518,"output":706,"cacheRead":28416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29640,"cost":{"input":0.00007252,"output":0.00019768000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0007956479999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0010658479999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778753092425,"responseId":"fc5d0836-c280-40d4-b5d4-622aca99bfb2"}}
