{"type":"message","id":"7e954cbe","parentId":"ad2406c0","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:06:32.032Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. The project has `GASDK` in its scripting defines (hard-coded in ProjectSettings.asset for Standalone builds), which causes `ChannelMacro_GASDK.cs` and `SDKInit.cs` to try to compile the `using GiantSDK.Parent;` directive. But the GiantSDK plugin source files are in `OtherPlugins\\GASDK\\GiantSDK\\` and not in the `Assets` folder.\n\nLooking at all the SDK configs, none of them seem to copy the GiantSDK source code (namespace `GiantSDK.Parent`) into the Assets folder. They only copy platform-specific plugins.\n\nThe solution is to either:\n1. Remove the `GASDK` define from the Standalone platform scripting symbols\n2. Or copy the GiantSDK wrapper source files into Assets\n\nLet me check what's actually in OtherPlugins/GASDK/GiantSDK/ - these are just C# wrappers/source files.\n\nActually wait - let me re-examine. The files `OtherPlugins\\GASDK\\GiantSDK\\` have `namespace GiantSDK.Parent`. These are wrapper scripts that compile in the editor. For this to work, they need to be somewhere Unity will compile them.\n\nLet me check `BuildPipelineMethod_Assetbundle.cs` to see if there's a step that copies these.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_cHWsyehfFBgHKczl7BmP6809","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\Assets\\Editor\\BuildPipeline\\Method\\BuildPipelineMethod_Assetbundle.cs\" -TotalCount 60","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":6132,"output":397,"cacheRead":42368,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48897,"cost":{"input":0.00085848,"output":0.00011116000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001186304,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002155944}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778753187379,"responseId":"23d3629a-037f-4679-82ba-6e7f1a621ac4"}}
