{"type":"message","id":"798499f6","parentId":"5d265405","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:06:46.213Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the GiantSDK source files are in `OtherPlugins\\GASDK\\GiantSDK\\` and they use `namespace GiantSDK.Parent`. These need to be copied into the Assets folder for Unity to compile them.\n\nActually, I just realized - looking at the project settings output again:\n\n```\nscriptingDefineSymbols:\n    1: UNITY_POST_PROCESSING_STACK_V2;AMPLIFY_SHADER_EDITOR;TextMeshPro;GASDK;GuanFang;CRASH_SIGHT;PerfSight\n    4: TextMeshPro;GASDK;GuanFang;CRASH_SIGHT;PerfSight\n    7: UNITY_POST_PROCESSING_STACK_V2;AMPLIFY_SHADER_EDITOR;ENABLE_HYBRIDCLR;ENABLE_ERROR_AND_ABOVE_LOG;GM_COMMOND;TESTIN;LOGGER_ON;ALLLOG;TESTRATE;ENABLE_LOG;HOTFIX_ENABLE;GASDK;GuanFang;CRASH_SIGHT;PerfSight;TextMeshPro\n```\n\nPlatform 1 = Standalone (Windows, Mac, Linux). Platform 4 = Android. Platform 7 = Android (again). \n\nThe `GASDK` define is set on platforms 1, 4, and 7. Since we're running in batch mode on Windows (Standalone), platform 1 is active with `GASDK` defined.\n\nThe GiantSDK scripts are not in Assets. I need to copy them there for the compiler to find them. Or I need to remove the `GASDK` define from platform 1.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. This is a hot update pipeline - it only builds asset bundles, not player code. The GASDK define doesn't make sense for a hot update pipeline. Perhaps the developer usually has the SDK files already in Assets (from running the editor normally with an SDK plan applied), and they got git-cleaned at some point.\n\nLet me just copy the GiantSDK source files into a suitable location in Assets. The most appropriate place would be `Assets/Plugins/GiantSDK` or similar.\n\nActually, I just realized - the Pipeline is going to just build asset bundles for the hot update. The GiantSDK is only needed for platform-specific builds (Android, iOS, etc.). For a simple hot update (asset bundle build), we don't actually need the GASDK define at all.\n\nThe simplest fix would be to temporarily remove the `GASDK` define from the scripting symbols for the Standalone platform. But I'm not sure if the pipeline needs it.\n\nWait, let me check what the hot update pipeline actually does. Let me look for the `RunHotUpdatePipeline` method.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_nNqozk3QPQ6gxvaXTjNi5552","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Path \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\Assets\" -Recurse -Filter \"*.cs\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-String -Pattern \"RunHotUpdatePipeline\" -SimpleMatch | Select-Object -First 5 -ExpandProperty Path","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":546,"output":720,"cacheRead":50048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51314,"cost":{"input":0.00007644,"output":0.00020160000000000002,"cacheRead":0.001401344,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001679384}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778753199155,"responseId":"d625f50f-c720-404a-947f-f4b8797c5602"}}
