{"type":"message","id":"9d1e956e","parentId":"0a5fb47b","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:09:17.077Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, let me also check if there are other platforms that might be affected. When running in batch mode, Unity uses the Standalone platform by default. But let me also check what platform 7 (Android with lots of defines) is about.\n\nActually, in Unity 2020, the build target is determined by the `-buildTarget` parameter. Since we didn't pass one, it defaults to the active platform selected in the Editor (which could be Standalone).\n\nAlso, platform 1 in the scripting defines is Standalone. So removing the SDK defines from platform 1 should fix the compilation for Standalone. Let me try.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Iu6O02BYOxHAOmSBHJFd0392","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"& \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Unity.exe\" -batchmode -quit -nographics -projectPath \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\" -executeMethod YYZY.BuildPipeline.BuildPipeline.RunHotUpdatePipeline -logFile \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\"","timeout":7200,"yieldMs":300000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":33,"output":307,"cacheRead":67328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67668,"cost":{"input":0.000004620000000000001,"output":0.00008596000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001885184,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001975764}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778753353536,"responseId":"857bc80f-86ac-4eaf-aa08-49f5d30af81a"}}
