{"type":"message","id":"0c21fa6a","parentId":"ff1d9e76","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:10:00.292Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the `PerfSight` define is case-sensitive! The file uses `#if PerfSight` but the define is `PerfSight` (capital P, capital S). Let me check the actual define from project settings.\n\nLooking at the project settings:\n```\nPerfSight\n```\n\nAnd the file uses:\n```\n#if PerfSight\n```\n\nThese match. So `PerfSight` should be defined in the project settings for platform 4 and 7, but NOT for platform 1 (Standalone) since I removed it.\n\nBut the error says `error CS0103: The name 'PerfSightAgent' does not exist in the current context` at line 10 of the file. Line 10 in the file would be inside the `#if PerfSight` block. If `PerfSight` is NOT defined, the code shouldn't be compiled.\n\nWait, let me look at the file more carefully:\n\n```\n#if PerfSight\n```\n\nCould it be that `PerfSight` is somehow defined somewhere else? Maybe not in scripting defines but through some other mechanism?\n\nActually, let me look at the log more carefully. The log has NUMBERS like lines 834 and 944. Looking at the log... maybe these are errors from TWO separate compilation passes - perhaps Unity compiles for both the editor (Editor platform) and the standalone player separately.\n\nActually, looking at the log pattern - I see the same errors twice, which might be two compilation passes. This is normal for Unity compilation.\n\nBut why is `PerfSight` still defined? Let me check if there might be a csc.rsp or other mechanism that defines it. Or maybe the `PerfSight` define is also coming from somewhere else.\n\nLet me check if there's a `PerfSight` define in the asmdef or in a response file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_rwA9kX8Ftu3vDHKUqv892905","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\" -Filter \"*.rsp\" -Recurse -ErrorAct