{"type":"message","id":"ef7188a4","parentId":"e05746bd","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:10:10.373Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The defineConstraints are empty. So the defines should come from project settings only.\n\nLet me check what platform Unity is building for. Maybe Unity is defaulting to a different platform than Standalone. Let me check which build targets correspond to these numbers.\n\nUnity platform build target numbers:\n- 1: Standalone (Windows, Mac, Linux)\n- 4: Android\n- 7: Android (sub-target?)\n- 13: iOS\n- 14: iOS (arm64)\n- 19: WebGL\n- 21: Xbox One or other\n\nSo platform 1 (Standalone) should be correct. Let me check if maybe Unity defaults to a different target without -buildTarget.\n\nActually, let me check - in Unity 2020.3, the batch mode defaults to the currently selected build target in the Editor. Let me check what the current build target is.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_WMLqEqTWsqptFoKrJjup3036","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\ProjectSettings\\ProjectSettings.asset\" -Pattern \"buildTarget:\" -Context 0,1","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":405,"output":282,"cacheRead":76416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77103,"cost":{"input":0.0000567,"output":0.00007896,"cacheRead":0.002139648,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002275308}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778753406489,"responseId":"789f0611-3503-4666-91f4-06108a799fc1"}}
