{"type":"message","id":"c657bfe2","parentId":"13d34a9c","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:26:35.643Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the process exited with code 0, but the log still shows it was importing assets. It seems like Unity may have crashed or was killed before it could run the pipeline properly. But exit code 0 usually indicates success... \n\nWait, looking at the `-quit` flag in the command - Unity is supposed to quit after the executeMethod completes. But if the rest of the log just shows imports and no pipeline output, Unity might have quit before the pipeline method was actually called because the import was still in progress.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the exit code 0, this might mean Unity started, compiled scripts (success), but then the `-quit` flag caused it to quit before the pipeline finished importing and running.\n\nWait, no - the log has `===============Initialize BuildPipeline: Executing===============` at line 1339. This means the pipeline class was initialized. But the pipeline method might not have actually executed because the import hadn't finished yet.\n\nActually, Unity normally triggers the `-executeMethod` AFTER importing assets. So the import should complete first, then the method runs, then `-quit` exits. The exit code 0 suggests the pipeline method ran successfully.\n\nBut looking at the last log lines, they're all still asset imports. Let me look further back in the log to find where the pipeline method was called and what it produced.\n\nActually wait - the process exited with code 0 but no new output lines? That means either the pipeline finished silently (no output) after imports, or Unity completed and quit.\n\nLet me look for more pipeline-specific output.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_VO7Pc76PZZccRUqrNPnw0272","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_Run