{"type":"message","id":"ca1efc76","parentId":"ea36a570","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:35:38.897Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log ends abruptly in the middle of an import. There's no error message, no crash dump, nothing. Unity just exited with code 0.\n\nThis is suspicious. Let me check if perhaps Unity ran out of memory or there's a different issue. The Library cache might be corrupted from the previous run where Unity was killed.\n\nLet me take a completely different approach. Let me look at how the PowerShell script handles this - maybe there's a better way to manage the process.\n\nActually, wait - the file shows the import line is incomplete (ends with `using Guid(121623f88cf55d94d99f6cfb63da2c26) Importer(-1,00000000000000000000000000000000)` without a closing `-> (artifact id...)`. This means Unity was killed mid-write to the log file. \n\nThe process exited with code 0 somehow, but Unity crashed or was killed. Let me check if there's a Unity crash dump.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ntVmO1GLRmmb4XwR3wy02344","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\" -Filter \"*.dmp\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name; Get-ChildItem \"$env:TEMP\" -Filter \"Unity*.dmp\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":2094,"output":331,"cacheRead":117248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119673,"cost":{"input":0.00029316000000000005,"output":0.00009268,"cacheRead":0.003282944,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003668784}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778754935143,"responseId":"c49ba681-d7b4-40e6-9e90-bd64dcdf2ad8"}}
