{"type":"message","id":"43dd1624","parentId":"d6e16679","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:35:43.846Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No crash dumps. The process is exiting normally (code 0) but without completing the import. This might be because Unity decided to quit after the import \"pass\" completed but before actually calling the executeMethod.\n\nActually, in Unity batch mode, without `-quit`, Unity is supposed to keep running. Unless something causes it to exit.\n\nWait - there's something I missed. Unity batch mode without `-nographics` or with `-batchmode` keeps running. But if I look at the command: `-batchmode -nographics` - this should keep Unity running.\n\nHmm, actually let me check if there's an issue with the way the process is being tracked. Maybe OpenClaw's exec tool is killing the process after the yield period.\n\nThe process had `yieldMs: 600000` (10 minutes). After the initial 10 minutes, the output was captured. Then I used poll with timeout which should continue monitoring. Let me check if maybe the process manager killed it.\n\nLet me look at the process more carefully. The exec command said \"Command still running (session oceanic-sable, pid 19712)\" and then I polled multiple times. Eventually it said \"Process exited with code 0.\"\n\nLet me try a different approach entirely. Maybe I should use the PowerShell script approach as mentioned in TOOLS.md: `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\tools\\hotupdate-scripts\\UpdateTestServer.ps1\"`\n\nLet me check if that script exists.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_pAAG3rJlhFp3yuk7PxIq7527","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Test-Path \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\tools\\hotupdate-scripts\\UpdateTestServer.ps1\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":135,"output":411,"cacheRead":119552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120