{"type":"message","id":"43b33c5d","parentId":"4ab1f278","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:35:48.538Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The PowerShell script doesn't exist. Let me try yet another approach. The issue might be related to the Library being corrupted from the first run. Let me try a clean approach:\n\n1. First, copy the GiantSDK files to the correct location within the AOT assembly scope\n2. Clean the entire Library folder (not just ScriptAssemblies)\n3. Run Unity with the pipeline\n\nActually, I've already done most of this. The issue now is that Unity exits before executing the pipeline. Let me check if there's a way to make Unity wait for imports to finish.\n\nActually, I just realized something. The command I ran was without `-quit`. But the process still exited. This means Unity itself decided to exit. In batch mode without `-quit`, Unity will keep running until something tells it to quit.\n\nWait, there might be an Application.Quit() call somewhere in the initialization code that's triggered by the pipeline. Or Unity might be failing to load a required component.\n\nLet me try a completely clean run by deleting the Library folder.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_72JSPDb7xoDBW6oXwAiw5625","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Remove-Item -Path \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\Library\" -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue; Write-Host \"Library deleted\"","timeout":120}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":47,"output":319,"cacheRead":120064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120430,"cost":{"input":0.0000065800000000000005,"output":0.00008932,"cacheRead":0.0033617919999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0034576919999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778754944063,"responseId":"520a6c90-e9c3-4369-b4c8-58ff7b3b9a90"}}
