{"type":"message","id":"530d43e9","parentId":"8f9630ad","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:36:33.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the code! `RunHotUpdatePipeline` calls `BeginBatchCli(HotUpdatePipelineName, selectedOnly: false)`. And `BeginBatchCli` can call `EditorApplication.Exit(1)` if the pipeline name is empty. But more importantly, this is run via `Execute()` which uses `EditorCoroutine` and `EditorApplication.update`.\n\nThe key insight is that the method runs on the main thread and requires the `EditorApplication.update` loop to be running. But in batch mode, Unity runs the method and then immediately tries to import remaining assets rather than entering the update loop.\n\nWait, looking at `BeginBatchCli` - it probably starts a coroutine or sets up an update delegate, and then exits. But the method itself returns quickly.\n\nActually, the issue is clear now. The pipeline uses `-executeMethod` which calls `BeginBatchCli`, which sets up callbacks and then `-quit` tells Unity to quit. But the asset import needs to complete first. In the version without `-quit`, asset DB import is still blocking.\n\nLet me look at `BeginBatchCli` more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_nInEoQmClqaQrDOSfQJK5575","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\Assets\\Editor\\BuildPipeline\\BuildPipeline.cs","offset":122,"limit":80}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1910,"output":334,"cacheRead":121728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123972,"cost":{"input":0.0002674,"output":0.00009352000000000001,"cacheRead":0.003408384,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0037693040000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778754988898,"responseId":"9da067ea-304c-4d43-b7fb-aa32b0e5ad7e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7bebe301","parentId":"530d43e9","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:36:33.135Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_nInEoQmClqaQrDOSfQJK5575","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        private static void BeginBatchCli(string pipeline, bool selectedOnly)\n        {\n            if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(pipeline))\n            {\n                Debug.LogError(\"BuildPipeline CLI: pipeline name is empty.\");\n                EditorApplication.Exit(1);\n                return;\n            }\n\n            EditorPrefs.SetBool(BatchExitAfterDonePrefKey, true);\n            var mode = selectedOnly ? \"Selected\" : \"Full\";\n            Debug.Log($\"BuildPipeline CLI (batch) mode={mode} pipeline='{pipeline}'\");\n\n            var pipe = Config.GetPipeLine(pipeline);\n            if (pipe == null)\n            {\n                Debug.LogError(\"pipeline \" + pipeline + \" not found!\");\n                ClearBatchExitRequest();\n                EditorApplication.Exit(1);\n                return;\n            }\n\n            try\n            {\n                Config.ExecuteStack.Clear();\n                ExecutePipeline(pipe, selectedOnly);\n            }\n            catch (Exception e)\n            {\n                Debug.LogException(e);\n                ClearBatchExitRequest();\n                EditorApplication.Exit(1);\n                return;\n            }\n\n            TryBatchExitNowIfDone();\n        }\n\n        private static void ClearBatchExitRequest()\n        {\n            EditorPrefs.SetBool(BatchExitAfterDonePrefKey, false);\n        }\n\n        private static void TryBatchExitNowIfDone()\n        {\n            if (!EditorPrefs.GetBool(BatchExitAfterDonePrefKey, false))\n                return;\n            if (!IsDone())\n                return;\n\n            ClearBatchExitRequest();\n            var code = LastRunSucceeded ? 0 : 1;\n            if (code != 0)\n                Debug.LogError(\"Build pipeline finished with errors or was canceled.\");\n            EditorApplication.Exit(code);\n        }\n\n        public static void ExecuteSelected(string pipeline)\n        {\n            var pipe = Config.GetPipeLine(pipeline);\n            if (pipe != null)\n            {\n                Config.ExecuteStack.Clear();\n                ExecutePipeline(pipe, true);\n            }\n            else\n            {\n                Debug.Log(\"pipeline \" + pipeline + \" not found!\");\n            }\n        }\n\n        public static void SaveConfig()\n        {\n            if (config != null)\n            {\n                var path = ConfigFilePath;\n                using (var w = serializer.CreateWriter(File.OpenWrite(path)))\n                {\n                    w.Version = BuildPipelineConfig.APIConfigVersion;\n                    w.Write(BuildPipelineConfig.APIConfigVersion);\n\n[115 more lines in file. Use offset=202 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778754993135}}
{"type":"message","id":"cfe11c91","parentId":"7bebe301","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:36:40.216Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full flow!\n\n1. `RunHotUpdatePipeline()` is called via `-executeMethod`\n2. It detects batch mode and calls `BeginBatchCli(\"热更\", false)`\n3. `BeginBatchCli`:\n   - Sets `EditorPrefs.SetBool(BatchExitAfterDonePrefKey, true)`\n   - Calls `ExecutePipeline(pipe, false)`\n   - Then calls `TryBatchExitNowIfDone()`\n4. `TryBatchExitNowIfDone()`:\n   - Checks if `IsDone()` returns true\n   - If done, calls `EditorApplication.Exit(code)`\n\nThe key is `ExecutePipeline` which starts the pipeline execution. The pipeline runs asynchronously via EditorApplication.update delegates (coroutines). So:\n- `BeginBatchCli` starts the pipeline, then immediately calls `TryBatchExitNowIfDone()`\n- At this point, `IsDone()` is false because the pipeline is still running\n- So `TryBatchExitNowIfDone()` returns without calling `EditorApplication.Exit()`\n- The async pipeline execution continues\n- When the pipeline finishes, it should call `TryBatchExitNowIfDone()` again\n- But `-quit` was specified, causing Unity to quit before the pipeline finishes!\n\nWith `-quit`, Unity's batch mode quits the application after the first frame/update. The async pipeline might not have had a chance to finish before Unity exits.\n\nWithout `-quit`, Unity keeps running, but the pipeline might be blocked waiting for asset imports.\n\nThis is why the bat file has `-quit` - it's meant to work correctly when:\n1. Assets are already cached (not a first-time import)\n2. The pipeline finishes quickly\n\nBut on a first-time import, the pipeline never gets to execute because Unity is stuck importing assets.\n\nSo what I need to do is:\n1. Run Unity WITHOUT `-executeMethod` first to let all assets import\n2. Then run Unity WITH `-executeMethod` and `-quit` to run the pipeline\n\nLet me try this two-step approach.\n\nActually wait - looking at the bat file command:\n```\n\"%UNITY_PATH%\" -batchmode -quit -nographics -projectPath \"%PROJECT_PATH%\" -executeMethod YYZY.BuildPipeline.BuildPipeline.RunHotUpdatePipeline -logFile \"%LOG_FILE%\"\n```\n\nThis should work on subsequent runs (non-first-time) because assets are already cached. The first-time import is the bottleneck.\n\nLet me run Unity without executeMethod first to import all assets.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Understood the pipeline flow. Let me first import all assets by running Unity without executeMethod, then run the pipeline."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_DA19vHG9au0CaY30EZhK5891","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"& \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Unity.exe\" -batchmode -quit -nographics -projectPath \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\" -logFile \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_Import.log\"","timeout":10800,"yieldMs":1200000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":582,"output":712,"cacheRead":123904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125198,"cost":{"input":0.00008148,"output":0.00019936000000000002,"cacheRead":0.003469312,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003750152}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778754993138,"responseId":"6bbd0341-1f46-4ac4-ad8c-4c7547c582ff"}}
